Bronze resembling the Campanian is ploduced in many parts of Italy and the provinces, but there they add only eight pounds of lead, and do additional smelting with charcoal ὸ because of their shortage of wood. The difference produced by this is noticed specially in Gaul, where the meta] is smelted between stones heated red hot, as this roasting scorches it and renders it black and friable. Moreover they only smelt it again once whereas to repeat this several times contributes a great deal to the quality.
